{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"kind":"attribute","text":"nonisolated"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"fixedSize"},{"kind":"text","text":"() -> "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"some"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/View","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewP","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"View"},{"kind":"text","text":"\n"}]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Return Value","anchor":"return-value"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A view that fixes this view at its ideal size.","type":"text"}]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"discussion","text":"Discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"During the layout of the view hierarchy, each view proposes a size to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"each child view it contains. If the child view doesn’t need a fixed size","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"it can accept and conform to the size offered by the parent.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For example, a "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Text"},{"type":"text","text":" view placed in an explicitly sized frame wraps"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and truncates its string to remain within its parent’s bounds:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["Text(\"A single line of text, too long to fit in a box.\")","    .frame(width: 200, height: 200)","    .border(Color.gray)"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"fixedSize()"},{"type":"text","text":" modifier can be used to create a view that maintains"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"ideal size"}]},{"type":"text","text":" of its children both dimensions:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["Text(\"A single line of text, too long to fit in a box.\")","    .fixedSize()","    .frame(width: 200, height: 200)","    .border(Color.gray)"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This can result in the view exceeding the parent’s bounds, which may or","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"may not be the effect you want."}]},{"inlineContent":[],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"You can think of ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"fixedSize()"},{"text":" as the creation of a ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"counter proposal"}]},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"to the view size proposed to a view by its parent. The ideal size of a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"view, and the specific effects of ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"fixedSize()"},{"text":" depends on the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"particular view and how you have configured it.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"To create a view that fixes the view’s size in either the horizontal or","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"vertical dimensions, see ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/View\/fixedSize(horizontal:vertical:)","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":".","type":"text"}]}]}],"sections":[],"metadata":{"remoteSource":{"url":"https:\/\/github.com\/OpenSwiftUIProject\/OpenSwiftUI\/blob\/main\/Sources\/OpenSwiftUICore\/Layout\/FixedSizeLayout.swift#L144","fileName":"FixedSizeLayout.swift"},"extendedModule":"OpenSwiftUICore","platforms":[{"deprecated":false,"unavail